<subSubSection id="64D95D0A94B59691B6982AE4A7A31E6B" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="CCBE35DD5BCD1C30B16495C7FA1FB9EB" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="52839EA4EC34172D04416CC327CB1012" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
An east Mediterranean element previously known from Central and West Anatolia (Turkey) and the Greek Island of Lesvos (
<bibRefCitation id="A502029060FF12F416131A88185DA68A" author="Chamberlain, D. F." journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7667910" refString="Chamberlain, D. F., 1972. Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands Vol. 4. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" title="Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands Vol. 4" year="1972">Chamberlain 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B6791AA4425BD3C26E2BCE1AD393BBCF" author="Hart, H. ' t" journalOrPublisher="ARG Gantner Verlag KG, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7669562" refString="Hart, H. 't, 2002. Flora Hellenica 2. ARG Gantner Verlag KG, Ruggell" title="Flora Hellenica 2" year="2002">Hart 2002</bibRefCitation>
). It was recently reported from Bulgaria (
<bibRefCitation id="B69A815E62B560C646599A74A475473E" author="Dimitrov, D." journalOrPublisher="Willdenowia, 40 (2): 189 - 204" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668000" refString="Dimitrov, D., 2010. Med-Checklist Notulae 29. Willdenowia, 40 (2): 189-204" title="Med-Checklist Notulae 29" year="2010">Dimitrov 2010</bibRefCitation>
), from a locality ca. 60 km NW of the Greek records presented above. The name of the species derives from the characteristic conferted inflorescence. Our collections from Nomos Evrou (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7932C7EC4150A6C3E011D29A46F47ED2" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F7677673" captionText="Figure 18. Sedum confertiflorum from Nomos Evrou (photo: P. Doumas)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/640558" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">18</figureCitation>
) are the first for continental Greece and the floristic region of the NE alike (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3D812495C19E0BE37FE14A71434ACCE8" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7677547" captionText="Figure 3. Distribution map of Trachomitum venetum, Sedum confertiflorum and Saxifraga sibirica in Greece." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/656543" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
